    {
      "id": "25Rz5mvafy4kuRh703p-b",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -223.4166666666659,
      "y": 287.8333333333335,
      "width": 1099.939208984375,
      "height": 1675,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2034348535,
      "version": 2914,
      "versionNonce": 2047151924,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1776705809052,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Functional Requirements\n- Users can save a word they found while reading a book.\n- System fetches and stores definitions for a word from an external dictionary API\n- Users can view saved words for a book.\n- Users can search books\n- Users can associated words with a book.\n- Books can have Authors 1 - many each way.\n- Users can rate and review books\n- Users can see their history of words added.\n\n\nNon-Functional Requirements\n- Scalability (more lookups than writes)\n- Support millions of users but modest QPS initially\n- Graceful fallback if Dictionary API fails\n- Simple and maintainable monolith design\n- Performance ( Word lookup latency < 200ms cached, 500ms for API call)\n- Consistency Eventual consistency is fine for review, word lists.\n- Reliability  No data loss for saved words\n- Extensibility Ability to swap dictionary APIs\n- Add new content types later\n\n\n---- \nOut of scope:\nReal-time collaboration\nSocial features ( follows, feeds etc. )\nComplex NLP or word recommendations.\nOffline Sync\nFault Tolerance\nGDPR Compliance\n\n\n\nCore Entities\n- User ( user_id, name, email, created_at )\n- Word (word_id, text, language) (Word can have multiple definitions so keep them separate )\n- UserWord ( id, user_id, word_id, book_id, saved_at, notes ) ( multiple users could enter the same word )\n- Definition ( cached from API ) (wrod_id, definition_text, part_of_speech, example, source_api, cached_at )\n- Book (book_id, title, author_id)\n- Author (author_id, name)\n- Review ( review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, comment, created_at )\n\n\n\nWeb/Controller Layer/Spring MVC Controllers\n\nBrowser -> Spring MVC Controllers -> Services -> Repositories/ DAOs -> DB\n\n\nTodo Later:\nCaching definitions to avoid repeated external API calls.\n\n\nAPI Controllers\n\nPOST /words -> save a word\nGET /words -> list saved words \nGET /books/{id} -> view book\nGET /books/search?q=....\n\n    \n\n\n\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 1668,
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Functional Requirements\n- Users can save a word they found while reading a book.\n- System fetches and stores definitions for a word from an external dictionary API\n- Users can view saved words for a book.\n- Users can search books\n- Users can associated words with a book.\n- Books can have Authors 1 - many each way.\n- Users can rate and review books\n- Users can see their history of words added.\n\n\nNon-Functional Requirements\n- Scalability (more lookups than writes)\n- Support millions of users but modest QPS initially\n- Graceful fallback if Dictionary API fails\n- Simple and maintainable monolith design\n- Performance ( Word lookup latency < 200ms cached, 500ms for API call)\n- Consistency Eventual consistency is fine for review, word lists.\n- Reliability  No data loss for saved words\n- Extensibility Ability to swap dictionary APIs\n- Add new content types later\n\n\n---- \nOut of scope:\nReal-time collaboration\nSocial features ( follows, feeds etc. )\nComplex NLP or word recommendations.\nOffline Sync\nFault Tolerance\nGDPR Compliance\n\n\n\nCore Entities\n- User ( user_id, name, email, created_at )\n- Word (word_id, text, language) (Word can have multiple definitions so keep them separate )\n- UserWord ( id, user_id, word_id, book_id, saved_at, notes ) ( multiple users could enter the same word )\n- Definition ( cached from API ) (wrod_id, definition_text, part_of_speech, example, source_api, cached_at )\n- Book (book_id, title, author_id)\n- Author (author_id, name)\n- Review ( review_id, user_id, book_id, rating, comment, created_at )\n\n\n\nWeb/Controller Layer/Spring MVC Controllers\n\nBrowser -> Spring MVC Controllers -> Services -> Repositories/ DAOs -> DB\n\n\nTodo Later:\nCaching definitions to avoid repeated external API calls.\n\n\nAPI Controllers\n\nPOST /words -> save a word\nGET /words -> list saved words \nGET /books/{id} -> view book\nGET /books/search?q=....\n\n    \n\n\n\n\n",
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
